# Testing

## Strategy

- **Integration-first:** Prefer tests that run real Prisma + migrations and Nest module wiring. Stub or fake only at boundaries (**GitHub scout**, **Vibe Kanban HTTP client**, **`gh` CLI**) so CI does not hit real networks.
- **Unit tests:** Use for **pure logic**, **Zod/schemas**, and **small helpers**—not for every controller line. HTTP smoke and API contracts live in `apps/server/test/*.integration-spec.ts` (e.g. `ui-smoke.integration-spec.ts`).

## Where files live

| Kind | Location | Jest |
|------|-----------|------|
| Unit | `apps/server/src/**/__tests__/**/*.spec.ts` (mirror the feature folder; root app spec in `apps/server/src/__tests__/`) | `pnpm test` — see `apps/server/package.json` `jest.testMatch` |
| Integration | `apps/server/test/*.integration-spec.ts` | `pnpm run test:integration` — `apps/server/test/jest-integration.json` |

New unit specs **must** sit under `__tests__` or Jest will not discover them. Imports from `__tests__` typically use `../` to the implementation module (adjust depth for nested folders). Keep the `*.spec.ts` suffix.

## Config (source of truth)

- **`apps/server/package.json` → `jest`:** `rootDir` `src`, `testMatch` for `__tests__` only, `collectCoverageFrom` excludes `*.spec.ts` and `generated/`.
- Do not colocate `*.spec.ts` next to `*.ts` sources under `apps/server/src/`.

## Coverage (optional)

Repo-wide line % is misleading; if you add thresholds, scope them to **directories that matter** (e.g. `sync/poll-cycle`). `apps/server/src/generated/**` is already excluded from coverage collection.

## When extending tests

- Add **integration** coverage for new **high-value flows** (persistence, sync outcomes, settings/mappings) before piling on isolated unit mocks.
- For new **HTTP routes**, consider **Supertest** + `INestApplication` + temp DB as the next investment (see existing `apps/server/test/` patterns).

## Verify

```bash
pnpm test && pnpm run test:cov && pnpm run test:integration
```
